text: Lake Alice (Glazier) as depicted in Sword and pen - or, Ventures and adventures of Willard Glazier in war and literature (1890) Lake Alice is a lake in Hubbard County, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. Lake Alice was named for Alice Glazier, the daughter of Minnesota explorer Captain Willard Glazier. ==See also== *List of lakes in Minnesota ==References== Category:Lakes of Minnesota Category:Lakes of Hubbard County, Minnesota
title: Lake Alice (Hubbard County, Minnesota)
